post_text: The President of the United States has proclaimed today, September 11, 2020, Patriot Day, in honor of those whose lives we remember on this 19th anniversary since the terrorist attack of September 11, 2001. Because today’s generation has no firsthand knowledge of the 9-11 tragedy, each year, we honor those who were lost, and all brave defenders of our freedom heritage. Let September 11, Patriot Day, be a day of national reflection on the American promise, and our role as citizens in upholding that promise.

post_text: Today LEUSD has announced reopening in a full distance learning model commencing August 12, 2020, with the goal of phasing to in-person learning via hybrid model and potentially full traditional later during the 2020-21 school year. The priority for reopening schools will be: 1) health and safety of all concerned, 2) high-quality teacher led instruction, and 3) equipping students, parents, teachers, and the community with instructional and social-emotional supports going forward.

If you have returning or new students who will be in Transitional Kinder–Grade 12 this fall, please complete our online registration & annual update via the Infinite Campus Parent Portal. Include returning students and new students (e.g., a younger sibling) on the same application, plus any changes to home address, phone number, and emergency contacts.
To request an active Parent Portal account or assistance with your application, leave a message with the Registration Processing Office at 951-253-7057. Sorry, walk-in support at the DO is temporarily suspended under COVID-19 orders. Our registration quick start page is linked below. Stay safe!

post_text: This is Teacher Appreciation Week, and May 13, next Wednesday, is California Day of the Teacher. LEUSD’s message to parents, students and teachers is simply, do everything with love. That’s what gets us through challenging times, it’s what makes the journey memorable, and it’s one thing that will never be in short supply when we team up to grow our children and shape their futures. Thank you, we honor you!

post_text: To LEUSD’s faith-based communities, we know the importance of this week and the days ahead. In your thoughts and meditations, please place on your heart the word “accompaniment.” It means “presence with another.” The COVID-19 pandemic has forced us to step into new roles as problem solvers, home schoolers, cheer leaders, healers, innovators, creators, essential providers and survivors. But today, let us receive the commission of accompaniment. Be fully present and in the moment with others—accompaniment; make a point to check in on those you don’t see every day—accompaniment; play, sing, and read together—accompaniment. Find someone who needs reassurance right now and offer it—accompaniment.

post_text: If you are leaving your home to attend any LEUSD Grab 'n Go free student meal events, please read. Yesterday, March 31, 2020, The Riverside University Health System-Public Health issued a recommendation for residents to cover their nose and mouth when leaving home for essential travel, such as grocery shopping or pharmacy visits. Effective face coverings do not have to be hospital grade, but need to cover the nose and mouth. For example, bandanas, fabric masks and neck gaiters are acceptable. We advise the above protection against COVID-19 spread be worn when attending LEUSD Grab 'n Go meal distribution events. Thank you.

post_text: To our LEUSD school community, we cannot thank you enough for your patience and support as we work together to ensure the safety of our students, staff, and families. This is to explain a change to our regularly scheduled Spring Recess, from March 16 – March 20, 2020, in coordination with local health authorities and the Riverside County Office of Education. To limit the spread of novel coronavirus, COVID-19, county wide school closures will be ordered effective Monday, March 16 through - April 3, 2020. During these times, all school related activities, including athletics, childcare, Think Together, community facilities use, and instruction, shall be canceled. Instruction is scheduled to resume on April 6, 2020. Additional information will be published early next week, so please check ParentSquare and LEUSD school and district websites for important updates. Again, thank you for supporting these unprecedented actions, and difficult decisions, which are necessary for the protection of all school stakeholders and public health. Respectfully, Dr. Doug Kimberly Superintendent
